The paper deals with the formal properties of a measure calculated from the output distribution of small Turing machines, which is related to lossless compression algorithms and algorithmic complexity. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the properties of a computable measure and its approximations, rather than on specific applications or algorithms, cs.IT and cs.DS seem to be the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are not directly related to the main topic of the paper.
